50 // A helper class to simplify the process of reducing a single binop node with a
51 // JSOperator. This class manages the rewriting of context, control, and effect
52 // dependencies during lowering of a binop and contains numerous helper
53 // functions for matching the types of inputs to an operation.
54 class JSBinopReduction final {
55  public:
56  JSBinopReduction(JSTypedLowering* lowering, Node* node)
57  : lowering_(lowering), node_(node) {}
58 
59  bool GetCompareNumberOperationHint(NumberOperationHint* hint) {
60  DCHECK_EQ(1, node_->op()->EffectOutputCount());
61  switch (GetCompareOperationHint(node_)) {
62  case CompareOperationHint::kSignedSmall:
63  *hint = NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall;
64  return true;
65  case CompareOperationHint::kNumber:
66  *hint = NumberOperationHint::kNumber;
67  return true;
68  case CompareOperationHint::kNumberOrBoolean:
69  *hint = NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrBoolean;
70  return true;
71  case CompareOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball:
72  *hint = NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball;
73  return true;
74  case CompareOperationHint::kAny:
75  case CompareOperationHint::kNone:
76  case CompareOperationHint::kString:
77  case CompareOperationHint::kSymbol:
78  case CompareOperationHint::kBigInt:
79  case CompareOperationHint::kBigInt64:
80  case CompareOperationHint::kReceiver:
81  case CompareOperationHint::kReceiverOrNullOrUndefined:
82  case CompareOperationHint::kStringOrOddball:
83  case CompareOperationHint::kInternalizedString:
84  break;
85  }
86  return false;
87  }
88 
89  bool GetCompareBigIntOperationHint(BigIntOperationHint* hint) {
90  DCHECK_EQ(1, node_->op()->EffectOutputCount());
91  switch (GetCompareOperationHint(node_)) {
92  case CompareOperationHint::kSignedSmall:
93  case CompareOperationHint::kNumber:
94  case CompareOperationHint::kNumberOrBoolean:
95  case CompareOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball:
96  case CompareOperationHint::kAny:
97  case CompareOperationHint::kNone:
98  case CompareOperationHint::kString:
99  case CompareOperationHint::kSymbol:
100  case CompareOperationHint::kReceiver:
101  case CompareOperationHint::kReceiverOrNullOrUndefined:
102  case CompareOperationHint::kStringOrOddball:
103  case CompareOperationHint::kInternalizedString:
104  return false;
105  case CompareOperationHint::kBigInt:
106  *hint = BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt;
107  return true;
108  case CompareOperationHint::kBigInt64:
109  *hint = BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt64;
110  return true;
111  }
112  UNREACHABLE();
113  }

155  // Check if a string addition will definitely result in creating a ConsString,
156  // i.e. if the combined length of the resulting string exceeds the ConsString
157  // minimum length.
158  bool ShouldCreateConsString() {
159  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSAdd, node_->opcode());
160  DCHECK(OneInputIs(Type::String()));
161  if (node_->InputAt(1)->opcode() == IrOpcode::kNewConsString) {
162  // If the right hand side is a ConsString, then we can create a
163  // ConsString. This doesn't work with the left hand side, since the right
164  // hand side of a ConsString cannot be the empty string except when the
165  // left hand side is a SeqString or External string, but we don't know
166  // that here.
167  return true;
168  }
169  if (BothInputsAre(Type::String()) ||
170  GetBinaryOperationHint(node_) == BinaryOperationHint::kString) {
171  HeapObjectBinopMatcher m(node_);
172  JSHeapBroker* broker = lowering_->broker();
173  if (m.right().HasResolvedValue() && m.right().Ref(broker).IsString()) {
174  StringRef right_string = m.right().Ref(broker).AsString();
175  if (right_string.length() >= ConsString::kMinLength) return true;
176  }
177  if (m.left().HasResolvedValue() && m.left().Ref(broker).IsString()) {
178  StringRef left_string = m.left().Ref(broker).AsString();
179  if (left_string.length() >= ConsString::kMinLength) {
180  // The invariant for ConsString requires the left hand side to be
181  // a sequential or external string if the right hand side is the
182  // empty string. Since we don't know anything about the right hand
183  // side here, we must ensure that the left hand side satisfy the
184  // constraints independent of the right hand side.
185  return left_string.IsSeqString() || left_string.IsExternalString();
186  }
187  }
188  }
189  return false;
190  }

353  Node* l = left();

356  node_->ReplaceInput(1, l);

359  // Remove all effect and control inputs and outputs to this node and change
360  // to the pure operator {op}.
361  Reduction ChangeToPureOperator(const Operator* op, Type type = Type::Any()) {
362  DCHECK_EQ(0, op->EffectInputCount());
363  DCHECK_EQ(false, OperatorProperties::HasContextInput(op));
364  DCHECK_EQ(0, op->ControlInputCount());
365  DCHECK_EQ(2, op->ValueInputCount());
366 
367  // Remove the effects from the node, and update its effect/control usages.
368  if (node_->op()->EffectInputCount() > 0) {
369  lowering_->RelaxEffectsAndControls(node_);
370  }
371  // Remove the inputs corresponding to context, effect, and control.
372  NodeProperties::RemoveNonValueInputs(node_);
373  // Remove the feedback vector input, if applicable.
374  if (JSOperator::IsBinaryWithFeedback(node_->opcode())) {
375  node_->RemoveInput(JSBinaryOpNode::FeedbackVectorIndex());
376  }
377  // Finally, update the operator to the new one.
378  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node_, op);
379 
380  // TODO(jarin): Replace the explicit typing hack with a call to some method
381  // that encapsulates changing the operator and re-typing.
382  Type node_type = NodeProperties::GetType(node_);
383  NodeProperties::SetType(node_, Type::Intersect(node_type, type, zone()));
384 
385  return lowering_->Changed(node_);
386  }
387 
388  Reduction ChangeToSpeculativeOperator(const Operator* op, Type upper_bound) {
389  DCHECK_EQ(1, op->EffectInputCount());
390  DCHECK_EQ(1, op->EffectOutputCount());
391  DCHECK_EQ(false, OperatorProperties::HasContextInput(op));
392  DCHECK_EQ(1, op->ControlInputCount());
393  DCHECK_EQ(0, op->ControlOutputCount());
394  DCHECK_EQ(0, OperatorProperties::GetFrameStateInputCount(op));
395  DCHECK_EQ(2, op->ValueInputCount());
396 
397  DCHECK_EQ(1, node_->op()->EffectInputCount());
398  DCHECK_EQ(1, node_->op()->EffectOutputCount());
399  DCHECK_EQ(1, node_->op()->ControlInputCount());
400 
401  // Reconnect the control output to bypass the IfSuccess node and
402  // possibly disconnect from the IfException node.
403  lowering_->RelaxControls(node_);
404 
405  // Remove the frame state and the context.
406  if (OperatorProperties::HasFrameStateInput(node_->op())) {
407  node_->RemoveInput(NodeProperties::FirstFrameStateIndex(node_));
408  }
409  node_->RemoveInput(NodeProperties::FirstContextIndex(node_));
410 
411  // Remove the feedback vector input, if applicable.
412  if (JSOperator::IsBinaryWithFeedback(node_->opcode())) {
413  node_->RemoveInput(JSBinaryOpNode::FeedbackVectorIndex());
414  }
415  // Finally, update the operator to the new one.
416  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node_, op);
417 
418  // Update the type to number.
419  Type node_type = NodeProperties::GetType(node_);
420  NodeProperties::SetType(node_,
421  Type::Intersect(node_type, upper_bound, zone()));
422 
423  return lowering_->Changed(node_);
424  }

426  const Operator* NumberOp() {
427  switch (node_->opcode()) {
428  case IrOpcode::kJSAdd:
429  return simplified()->NumberAdd();
430  case IrOpcode::kJSSubtract:
431  return simplified()->NumberSubtract();
432  case IrOpcode::kJSMultiply:
433  return simplified()->NumberMultiply();
434  case IrOpcode::kJSDivide:
435  return simplified()->NumberDivide();
436  case IrOpcode::kJSModulus:
437  return simplified()->NumberModulus();
438  case IrOpcode::kJSExponentiate:
439  return simplified()->NumberPow();
440  case IrOpcode::kJSBitwiseAnd:
441  return simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd();
442  case IrOpcode::kJSBitwiseOr:
443  return simplified()->NumberBitwiseOr();
444  case IrOpcode::kJSBitwiseXor:
445  return simplified()->NumberBitwiseXor();
446  case IrOpcode::kJSShiftLeft:
447  return simplified()->NumberShiftLeft();
448  case IrOpcode::kJSShiftRight:
449  return simplified()->NumberShiftRight();
450  case IrOpcode::kJSShiftRightLogical:
451  return simplified()->NumberShiftRightLogical();
452  default:
453  break;
454  }
455  UNREACHABLE();
456  }

504  Node* ConvertPlainPrimitiveToNumber(Node* node) {
505  DCHECK(NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::PlainPrimitive()));
506  // Avoid inserting too many eager ToNumber() operations.
507  Reduction const reduction = lowering_->ReduceJSToNumberInput(node);
508  if (reduction.Changed()) return reduction.replacement();
509  if (NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Number())) {
510  return node;
511  }
512  return graph()->NewNode(simplified()->PlainPrimitiveToNumber(), node);
513  }
514 
515  Node* ConvertToUI32(Node* node, Signedness signedness) {
516  // Avoid introducing too many eager NumberToXXnt32() operations.
517  Type type = NodeProperties::GetType(node);
518  if (signedness == kSigned) {
519  if (!type.Is(Type::Signed32())) {
520  node = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberToInt32(), node);
521  }
522  } else {
523  DCHECK_EQ(kUnsigned, signedness);
524  if (!type.Is(Type::Unsigned32())) {
525  node = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberToUint32(), node);
526  }
527  }
528  return node;
529  }

531  CompareOperationHint GetCompareOperationHint(Node* node) const {
532  const FeedbackParameter& p = FeedbackParameterOf(node->op());
533  return lowering_->broker()->GetFeedbackForCompareOperation(p.feedback());
534  }

537  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node_, effect);
538  }

546 JSTypedLowering::JSTypedLowering(Editor* editor, JSGraph* jsgraph,
547  JSHeapBroker* broker, Zone* zone)
548  : AdvancedReducer(editor),
549  jsgraph_(jsgraph),
550  broker_(broker),
551  empty_string_type_(
552  Type::Constant(broker, broker->empty_string(), graph()->zone())),
553  pointer_comparable_type_(
554  Type::Union(Type::Union(Type::BooleanOrNullOrUndefined(),
555  Type::Hole(), graph()->zone()),
556  Type::Union(Type::SymbolOrReceiver(), empty_string_type_,
557  graph()->zone()),
558  graph()->zone())),
559  type_cache_(TypeCache::Get()) {}

561 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSBitwiseNot(Node* node) {
562  Node* input = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
563  Type input_type = NodeProperties::GetType(input);
564  if (input_type.Is(Type::PlainPrimitive())) {
565  // JSBitwiseNot(x) => NumberBitwiseXor(ToInt32(x), -1)
566  const FeedbackParameter& p = FeedbackParameterOf(node->op());
567  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 1, jsgraph()->SmiConstant(-1));
568  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->BitwiseXor(p.feedback()));
569  JSBinopReduction r(this, node);
570  r.ConvertInputsToNumber();
571  r.ConvertInputsToUI32(kSigned, kSigned);
572  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(r.NumberOp(), Type::Signed32());
573  }
574  return NoChange();
575 }

577 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSDecrement(Node* node) {
578  Node* input = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
579  Type input_type = NodeProperties::GetType(input);
580  if (input_type.Is(Type::PlainPrimitive())) {
581  // JSDecrement(x) => NumberSubtract(ToNumber(x), 1)
582  const FeedbackParameter& p = FeedbackParameterOf(node->op());
583  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 1, jsgraph()->OneConstant());
584  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->Subtract(p.feedback()));
585  JSBinopReduction r(this, node);
586  r.ConvertInputsToNumber();
587  DCHECK_EQ(simplified()->NumberSubtract(), r.NumberOp());
588  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(r.NumberOp(), Type::Number());
589  }
590  return NoChange();
591 }

593 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSIncrement(Node* node) {
594  Node* input = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
595  Type input_type = NodeProperties::GetType(input);
596  if (input_type.Is(Type::PlainPrimitive())) {
597  // JSIncrement(x) => NumberAdd(ToNumber(x), 1)
598  const FeedbackParameter& p = FeedbackParameterOf(node->op());
599  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 1, jsgraph()->OneConstant());
600  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->Add(p.feedback()));
601  JSBinopReduction r(this, node);
602  r.ConvertInputsToNumber();
603  DCHECK_EQ(simplified()->NumberAdd(), r.NumberOp());
604  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(r.NumberOp(), Type::Number());
605  }
606  return NoChange();
607 }

609 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSNegate(Node* node) {
610  Node* input = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
611  Type input_type = NodeProperties::GetType(input);
612  if (input_type.Is(Type::PlainPrimitive())) {
613  // JSNegate(x) => NumberMultiply(ToNumber(x), -1)
614  const FeedbackParameter& p = FeedbackParameterOf(node->op());
615  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 1, jsgraph()->SmiConstant(-1));
616  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->Multiply(p.feedback()));
617  JSBinopReduction r(this, node);
618  r.ConvertInputsToNumber();
619  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(r.NumberOp(), Type::Number());
620  }
621  return NoChange();

624 Reduction JSTypedLowering::GenerateStringAddition(
625  Node* node, Node* left, Node* right, Node* context, Node* frame_state,
626  Node** effect, Node** control, bool should_create_cons_string) {
627  // Compute the resulting length.
628  Node* left_length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), left);
629  Node* right_length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), right);
630  Node* length =
631  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), left_length, right_length);
632 
633  PropertyCellRef string_length_protector =
634  MakeRef(broker(), factory()->string_length_protector());
635  string_length_protector.CacheAsProtector(broker());
636 
637  if (string_length_protector.value(broker()).AsSmi() ==
638  Protectors::kProtectorValid) {
639  // We can just deoptimize if the {length} is out-of-bounds. Besides
640  // generating a shorter code sequence than the version below, this
641  // has the additional benefit of not holding on to the lazy {frame_state}
642  // and thus potentially reduces the number of live ranges and allows for
643  // more truncations.
644  length = *effect = graph()->NewNode(
645  simplified()->CheckBounds(FeedbackSource()), length,
646  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(String::kMaxLength + 1), *effect, *control);
647  } else {
648  // Check if we would overflow the allowed maximum string length.
649  Node* check =
650  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThanOrEqual(), length,
651  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(String::kMaxLength));
652  Node* branch =
653  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, *control);
654  Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
655  Node* efalse = *effect;
656  {
657  // Throw a RangeError in case of overflow.
658  Node* vfalse = efalse = if_false = graph()->NewNode(
659  javascript()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowInvalidStringLength),
660  context, frame_state, efalse, if_false);
661 
662  // Update potential {IfException} uses of {node} to point to the
663  // %ThrowInvalidStringLength runtime call node instead.
664  Node* on_exception = nullptr;
665  if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
666  NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(on_exception, vfalse);
667  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(on_exception, efalse);
668  if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), vfalse);
669  Revisit(on_exception);
670  }
671 
672  // The above %ThrowInvalidStringLength runtime call is an unconditional
673  // throw, making it impossible to return a successful completion in this
674  // case. We simply connect the successful completion to the graph end.
675  if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->Throw(), efalse, if_false);
676  MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), if_false);
677  }
678  *control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
679  length = *effect =
680  graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(type_cache_->kStringLengthType),
681  length, *effect, *control);
682  }
683  // TODO(bmeurer): Ideally this should always use StringConcat and decide to
684  // optimize to NewConsString later during SimplifiedLowering, but for that
685  // to work we need to know that it's safe to create a ConsString.
686  Operator const* const op = should_create_cons_string
687  ? simplified()->NewConsString()
688  : simplified()->StringConcat();
689  Node* value = graph()->NewNode(op, length, left, right);
690  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, *effect, *control);
691  return Replace(value);
692 }
693 
694 Node* JSTypedLowering::UnwrapStringWrapper(Node* string_or_wrapper,
695  Node** effect, Node** control) {
696  Node* check =
697  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsString(), string_or_wrapper);
698  Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, *control);
699 
700  Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
701  Node* etrue = *effect;
702  Node* vtrue = string_or_wrapper;
703 
704  // We just checked that the value is a string.
705  vtrue = etrue = graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::String()), vtrue,
706  etrue, if_true);
707 
708  Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
709  Node* efalse = *effect;
710 
711  Node* vfalse = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
712  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSPrimitiveWrapperValue()),
713  string_or_wrapper, *effect, *control);
714 
715  // The value read from a string wrapper is a string.
716  vfalse = efalse = graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::String()),
717  vfalse, efalse, if_false);
718 
719  *control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
720  *effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, *control);
721 
722  return graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
723  vtrue, vfalse, *control);
724 }

726 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSAdd(Node* node) {
727  JSBinopReduction r(this, node);
728  if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::Number())) {
729  // JSAdd(x:number, y:number) => NumberAdd(x, y)
730  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->NumberAdd(), Type::Number());
731  }
732  if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::PlainPrimitive()) &&
733  r.NeitherInputCanBe(Type::StringOrReceiver())) {
734  // JSAdd(x:-string, y:-string) => NumberAdd(ToNumber(x), ToNumber(y))
735  r.ConvertInputsToNumber();
736  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->NumberAdd(), Type::Number());
737  }
738 
739  // Strength-reduce if one input is already known to be a string.
740  if (r.LeftInputIs(Type::String())) {
741  // JSAdd(x:string, y) => JSAdd(x, JSToString(y))
742  Reduction const reduction = ReduceJSToStringInput(r.right());
743  if (reduction.Changed()) {
744  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, reduction.replacement(), 1);
745  }
746  } else if (r.RightInputIs(Type::String())) {
747  // JSAdd(x, y:string) => JSAdd(JSToString(x), y)
748  Reduction const reduction = ReduceJSToStringInput(r.left());
749  if (reduction.Changed()) {
750  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, reduction.replacement(), 0);
751  }
752  }
753 
754  PropertyCellRef to_primitive_protector =
755  MakeRef(broker(), factory()->string_wrapper_to_primitive_protector());
756  to_primitive_protector.CacheAsProtector(broker());
757  bool can_inline_string_wrapper_add = false;
758 
759  // Always bake in String feedback into the graph.
760  if (r.GetBinaryOperationHint(node) == BinaryOperationHint::kString) {
761  r.CheckInputsToString();
762  } else if (r.GetBinaryOperationHint(node) ==
763  BinaryOperationHint::kStringOrStringWrapper) {
764  can_inline_string_wrapper_add =
765  dependencies()->DependOnProtector(to_primitive_protector);
766  if (can_inline_string_wrapper_add) {
767  r.CheckInputsToStringOrStringWrapper();
768  }
769  }
770 
771  // Strength-reduce concatenation of empty strings if both sides are
772  // primitives, as in that case the ToPrimitive on the other side is
773  // definitely going to be a no-op.
774  if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::Primitive())) {
775  if (r.LeftInputIs(empty_string_type_)) {
776  // JSAdd("", x:primitive) => JSToString(x)
777  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInputs(node, r.right());
778  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->ToString());
779  NodeProperties::SetType(
780  node, Type::Intersect(r.type(), Type::String(), graph()->zone()));
781  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSToString(node));
782  } else if (r.RightInputIs(empty_string_type_)) {
783  // JSAdd(x:primitive, "") => JSToString(x)
784  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInputs(node, r.left());
785  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->ToString());
786  NodeProperties::SetType(
787  node, Type::Intersect(r.type(), Type::String(), graph()->zone()));
788  return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSToString(node));
789  }
790  }
791 
792  Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
793  Node* frame_state = NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node);
794  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
795  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
796 
797  // Lower to string addition if both inputs are known to be strings.
798  if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::String())) {
799  return GenerateStringAddition(node, r.left(), r.right(), context,
800  frame_state, &effect, &control,
801  r.ShouldCreateConsString());
802  } else if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::StringOrStringWrapper()) &&
803  can_inline_string_wrapper_add) {
804  // If the left hand side is a string wrapper, unwrap it.
805  Node* left_string = UnwrapStringWrapper(r.left(), &effect, &control);
806 
807  // If the right hand side is a string wrapper, unwrap it.
808  Node* right_string = UnwrapStringWrapper(r.right(), &effect, &control);
809 
810  // Generate the string addition.
811  return GenerateStringAddition(node, left_string, right_string, context,
812  frame_state, &effect, &control, false);
813  }
814 
815  // We never get here when we had String feedback.
816  DCHECK_NE(BinaryOperationHint::kString, r.GetBinaryOperationHint(node));
817  if (r.OneInputIs(Type::String())) {
818  StringAddFlags flags = STRING_ADD_CHECK_NONE;
819  if (!r.LeftInputIs(Type::String())) {
820  flags = STRING_ADD_CONVERT_LEFT;
821  } else if (!r.RightInputIs(Type::String())) {
822  flags = STRING_ADD_CONVERT_RIGHT;
823  }
824  Operator::Properties properties = node->op()->properties();
825  if (r.NeitherInputCanBe(Type::Receiver())) {
826  // Both sides are already strings, so we know that the
827  // string addition will not cause any observable side
828  // effects; it can still throw obviously.
829  properties = Operator::kNoWrite | Operator::kNoDeopt;
830  }
831 
832  // JSAdd(x:string, y) => CallStub[StringAdd](x, y)
833  // JSAdd(x, y:string) => CallStub[StringAdd](x, y)
834  Callable const callable = CodeFactory::StringAdd(isolate(), flags);
835  auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
836  graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
837  callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(),
838  CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState, properties);
839  DCHECK_EQ(1, OperatorProperties::GetFrameStateInputCount(node->op()));
840  node->RemoveInput(JSAddNode::FeedbackVectorIndex());
841  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 0,
842  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code()));
843  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, common()->Call(call_descriptor));
844  return Changed(node);
845  }
846  return NoChange();
847 }

880 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSComparison(Node* node) {
881  JSBinopReduction r(this, node);
882  if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::String())) {
883  // If both inputs are definitely strings, perform a string comparison.
884  const Operator* stringOp;
885  switch (node->opcode()) {
886  case IrOpcode::kJSLessThan:
887  stringOp = simplified()->StringLessThan();
888  break;
889  case IrOpcode::kJSGreaterThan:
890  stringOp = simplified()->StringLessThan();
891  r.SwapInputs(); // a > b => b < a
892  break;
893  case IrOpcode::kJSLessThanOrEqual:
894  stringOp = simplified()->StringLessThanOrEqual();
895  break;
896  case IrOpcode::kJSGreaterThanOrEqual:
897  stringOp = simplified()->StringLessThanOrEqual();
898  r.SwapInputs(); // a >= b => b <= a
899  break;
900  default:
901  return NoChange();
902  }
903  r.ChangeToPureOperator(stringOp);
904  return Changed(node);
905  }
906 
907  const Operator* less_than;
908  const Operator* less_than_or_equal;
909  if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::Signed32()) ||
910  r.BothInputsAre(Type::Unsigned32())) {
911  less_than = simplified()->NumberLessThan();
912  less_than_or_equal = simplified()->NumberLessThanOrEqual();
913  } else if (r.OneInputCannotBe(Type::StringOrReceiver()) &&
914  r.BothInputsAre(Type::PlainPrimitive())) {
915  r.ConvertInputsToNumber();
916  less_than = simplified()->NumberLessThan();
917  less_than_or_equal = simplified()->NumberLessThanOrEqual();
918  } else if (r.IsStringCompareOperation()) {
919  r.CheckInputsToString();
920  less_than = simplified()->StringLessThan();
921  less_than_or_equal = simplified()->StringLessThanOrEqual();
922  } else {
923  return NoChange();
924  }
925  const Operator* comparison;
926  switch (node->opcode()) {
927  case IrOpcode::kJSLessThan:
928  comparison = less_than;
929  break;
930  case IrOpcode::kJSGreaterThan:
931  comparison = less_than;
932  r.SwapInputs(); // a > b => b < a
933  break;
934  case IrOpcode::kJSLessThanOrEqual:
935  comparison = less_than_or_equal;
936  break;
937  case IrOpcode::kJSGreaterThanOrEqual:
938  comparison = less_than_or_equal;
939  r.SwapInputs(); // a >= b => b <= a
940  break;
941  default:
942  return NoChange();
943  }
944  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(comparison);
945 }

947 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSEqual(Node* node) {
948  JSBinopReduction r(this, node);
949 
950  if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::UniqueName())) {
951  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->ReferenceEqual());
952  }
953  if (r.IsInternalizedStringCompareOperation()) {
954  r.CheckInputsToInternalizedString();
955  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->ReferenceEqual());
956  }
957  if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::String())) {
958  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->StringEqual());
959  }
960  if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::Boolean())) {
961  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->ReferenceEqual());
962  }
963  if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::Receiver())) {
964  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->ReferenceEqual());
965  }
966  if (r.OneInputIs(Type::NullOrUndefined())) {
967  RelaxEffectsAndControls(node);
968  node->RemoveInput(r.LeftInputIs(Type::NullOrUndefined()) ? 0 : 1);
969  node->TrimInputCount(1);
970  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, simplified()->ObjectIsUndetectable());
971  return Changed(node);
972  }
973 
974  if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::Signed32()) ||
975  r.BothInputsAre(Type::Unsigned32())) {
976  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->NumberEqual());
977  } else if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::Number())) {
978  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->NumberEqual());
979  } else if (r.IsReceiverCompareOperation()) {
980  r.CheckInputsToReceiver();
981  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->ReferenceEqual());
982  } else if (r.IsReceiverOrNullOrUndefinedCompareOperation()) {
983  // Check that both inputs are Receiver, Null or Undefined.
984  r.CheckInputsToReceiverOrNullOrUndefined();
985 
986  // If one side is known to be a detectable receiver now, we
987  // can simply perform reference equality here, since this
988  // known detectable receiver is going to only match itself.
989  if (r.OneInputIs(Type::DetectableReceiver())) {
990  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->ReferenceEqual());
991  }
992 
993  // Known that both sides are Receiver, Null or Undefined, the
994  // abstract equality operation can be performed like this:
995  //
996  // if left == undefined || left == null
997  // then ObjectIsUndetectable(right)
998  // else if right == undefined || right == null
999  // then ObjectIsUndetectable(left)
1000  // else ReferenceEqual(left, right)
1001 #define __ gasm.
1002  JSGraphAssembler gasm(broker(), jsgraph(), jsgraph()->zone(),
1003  BranchSemantics::kJS);
1004  gasm.InitializeEffectControl(r.effect(), r.control());
1005 
1006  auto lhs = TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(r.left());
1007  auto rhs = TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(r.right());
1008 
1009  auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1010  auto check_undetectable = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1011 
1012  __ GotoIf(__ ReferenceEqual(lhs, __ UndefinedConstant()),
1013  &check_undetectable, rhs);
1014  __ GotoIf(__ ReferenceEqual(lhs, __ NullConstant()), &check_undetectable,
1015  rhs);
1016  __ GotoIf(__ ReferenceEqual(rhs, __ UndefinedConstant()),
1017  &check_undetectable, lhs);
1018  __ GotoIf(__ ReferenceEqual(rhs, __ NullConstant()), &check_undetectable,
1019  lhs);
1020  __ Goto(&done, __ ReferenceEqual(lhs, rhs));
1021 
1022  __ Bind(&check_undetectable);
1023  __ Goto(&done,
1024  __ ObjectIsUndetectable(check_undetectable.PhiAt<Object>(0)));
1025 
1026  __ Bind(&done);
1027  Node* value = done.PhiAt(0);
1028  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, gasm.effect(), gasm.control());
1029  return Replace(value);
1030 #undef __
1031  } else if (r.IsStringCompareOperation()) {
1032  r.CheckInputsToString();
1033  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->StringEqual());
1034  } else if (r.IsSymbolCompareOperation()) {
1035  r.CheckInputsToSymbol();
1036  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->ReferenceEqual());
1037  }
1038  return NoChange();
1039 }

1041 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSStrictEqual(Node* node) {
1042  JSBinopReduction r(this, node);
1043  if (r.type().IsSingleton()) {
1044  // Let ConstantFoldingReducer handle this.
1045  return NoChange();
1046  }
1047  if (r.left() == r.right()) {
1048  // x === x is always true if x != NaN
1049  Node* replacement = graph()->NewNode(
1050  simplified()->BooleanNot(),
1051  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsNaN(), r.left()));
1052  DCHECK(NodeProperties::GetType(replacement).Is(r.type()));
1053  ReplaceWithValue(node, replacement);
1054  return Replace(replacement);
1055  }
1056 
1057  if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::Unique())) {
1058  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->ReferenceEqual());
1059  }
1060  if (r.OneInputIs(pointer_comparable_type_)) {
1061  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->ReferenceEqual());
1062  }
1063  if (r.IsInternalizedStringCompareOperation()) {
1064  r.CheckInputsToInternalizedString();
1065  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->ReferenceEqual());
1066  }
1067  if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::String())) {
1068  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->StringEqual());
1069  }
1070  if (r.IsStringOrOddballCompareOperation()) {
1071  r.CheckInputsToStringOrOddball();
1072  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->StringOrOddballStrictEqual());
1073  }
1074  NumberOperationHint hint;
1075  BigIntOperationHint hint_bigint;
1076  if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::Signed32()) ||
1077  r.BothInputsAre(Type::Unsigned32())) {
1078  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->NumberEqual());
1079  } else if (r.GetCompareNumberOperationHint(&hint) &&
1080  hint != NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball &&
1081  hint != NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrBoolean) {
1082  // SpeculativeNumberEqual performs implicit conversion of oddballs to
1083  // numbers, so me must not generate it for strict equality with respective
1084  // hint.
1085  DCHECK(hint == NumberOperationHint::kNumber ||
1086  hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall);
1087  return r.ChangeToSpeculativeOperator(
1088  simplified()->SpeculativeNumberEqual(hint), Type::Boolean());
1089  } else if (r.BothInputsAre(Type::Number())) {
1090  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->NumberEqual());
1091  } else if (r.GetCompareBigIntOperationHint(&hint_bigint)) {
1092  DCHECK(hint_bigint == BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt ||
1093  hint_bigint == BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt64);
1094  return r.ChangeToSpeculativeOperator(
1095  simplified()->SpeculativeBigIntEqual(hint_bigint), Type::Boolean());
1096  } else if (r.IsReceiverCompareOperation()) {
1097  // For strict equality, it's enough to know that one input is a Receiver,
1098  // as a strict equality comparison with a Receiver can only yield true if
1099  // both sides refer to the same Receiver.
1100  r.CheckLeftInputToReceiver();
1101  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->ReferenceEqual());
1102  } else if (r.IsReceiverOrNullOrUndefinedCompareOperation()) {
1103  // For strict equality, it's enough to know that one input is a Receiver,
1104  // Null or Undefined, as a strict equality comparison with a Receiver,
1105  // Null or Undefined can only yield true if both sides refer to the same
1106  // instance.
1107  r.CheckLeftInputToReceiverOrNullOrUndefined();
1108  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->ReferenceEqual());
1109  } else if (r.IsStringCompareOperation()) {
1110  r.CheckInputsToString();
1111  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->StringEqual());
1112  } else if (r.IsSymbolCompareOperation()) {
1113  // For strict equality, it's enough to know that one input is a Symbol,
1114  // as a strict equality comparison with a Symbol can only yield true if
1115  // both sides refer to the same Symbol.
1116  r.CheckLeftInputToSymbol();
1117  return r.ChangeToPureOperator(simplified()->ReferenceEqual());
1118  }
1119  return NoChange();
1120 }

1125  if (input_type.Is(Type::Name())) {

1128  return Replace(input);

1130  return NoChange();

1133 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSToLength(Node* node) {
1134  Node* input = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
1135  Type input_type = NodeProperties::GetType(input);
1136  if (input_type.Is(type_cache_->kIntegerOrMinusZero)) {
1137  if (input_type.IsNone() || input_type.Max() <= 0.0) {
1138  input = jsgraph()->ZeroConstant();
1139  } else if (input_type.Min() >= kMaxSafeInteger) {
1140  input = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(kMaxSafeInteger);
1141  } else {
1142  if (input_type.Min() <= 0.0) {
1143  input = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberMax(),
1144  jsgraph()->ZeroConstant(), input);
1145  }
1146  if (input_type.Max() > kMaxSafeInteger) {
1147  input =
1148  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberMin(),
1149  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(kMaxSafeInteger), input);
1150  }
1151  }
1152  ReplaceWithValue(node, input);
1153  return Replace(input);
1154  }
1155  return NoChange();
1156 }

1158 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSToNumberInput(Node* input) {
1159  // Try constant-folding of JSToNumber with constant inputs.
1160  Type input_type = NodeProperties::GetType(input);
1161 
1162  if (input_type.Is(Type::String())) {
1163  HeapObjectMatcher m(input);
1164  if (m.HasResolvedValue() && m.Ref(broker()).IsString()) {
1165  StringRef input_value = m.Ref(broker()).AsString();
1166  std::optional<double> number = input_value.ToNumber(broker());
1167  if (!number.has_value()) return NoChange();
1168  return Replace(jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(number.value()));
1169  }
1170  }
1171  if (input_type.IsHeapConstant()) {
1172  HeapObjectRef input_value = input_type.AsHeapConstant()->Ref();
1173  double value;
1174  if (input_value.OddballToNumber(broker()).To(&value)) {
1175  return Replace(jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(value));
1176  }
1177  }
1178  if (input_type.Is(Type::Number())) {
1179  // JSToNumber(x:number) => x
1180  return Changed(input);
1181  }
1182  if (input_type.Is(Type::Undefined())) {
1183  // JSToNumber(undefined) => #NaN
1184  return Replace(jsgraph()->NaNConstant());
1185  }
1186  if (input_type.Is(Type::Null())) {
1187  // JSToNumber(null) => #0
1188  return Replace(jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
1189  }
1190  return NoChange();
1191 }

1193 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSToNumber(Node* node) {
1194  // Try to reduce the input first.
1195  Node* const input = node->InputAt(0);
1196  Reduction reduction = ReduceJSToNumberInput(input);
1197  if (reduction.Changed()) {
1198  ReplaceWithValue(node, reduction.replacement());
1199  return reduction;
1200  }
1201  Type const input_type = NodeProperties::GetType(input);
1202  if (input_type.Is(Type::PlainPrimitive())) {
1203  RelaxEffectsAndControls(node);
1204  node->TrimInputCount(1);
1205  // For a PlainPrimitive, ToNumeric is the same as ToNumber.
1206  Type node_type = NodeProperties::GetType(node);
1207  NodeProperties::SetType(
1208  node, Type::Intersect(node_type, Type::Number(), graph()->zone()));
1209  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, simplified()->PlainPrimitiveToNumber());
1210  return Changed(node);
1211  }
1212  return NoChange();
1213 }

1262 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSToStringInput(Node* input) {
1263  if (input->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToString) {
1264  // Recursively try to reduce the input first.
1265  Reduction result = ReduceJSToString(input);
1266  if (result.Changed()) return result;
1267  return Changed(input); // JSToString(JSToString(x)) => JSToString(x)
1268  }
1269  Type input_type = NodeProperties::GetType(input);
1270  if (input_type.Is(Type::String())) {
1271  return Changed(input); // JSToString(x:string) => x
1272  }
1273  if (input_type.Is(Type::Boolean())) {
1274  return Replace(graph()->NewNode(
1275  common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged), input,
1276  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(factory()->true_string()),
1277  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(factory()->false_string())));
1278  }
1279  if (input_type.Is(Type::Undefined())) {
1280  return Replace(
1281  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(factory()->undefined_string()));
1282  }
1283  if (input_type.Is(Type::Null())) {
1284  return Replace(jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(factory()->null_string()));
1285  }
1286  if (input_type.Is(Type::NaN())) {
1287  return Replace(jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(factory()->NaN_string()));
1288  }
1289  if (input_type.Is(Type::Number())) {
1290  return Replace(graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberToString(), input));
1291  }
1292  return NoChange();
1293 }

1307 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSToObject(Node* node) {
1308  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSToObject, node->opcode());
1309  Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
1310  Type receiver_type = NodeProperties::GetType(receiver);
1311  Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
1312  Node* frame_state = NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node);
1313  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
1314  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
1315  if (receiver_type.Is(Type::Receiver())) {
1316  ReplaceWithValue(node, receiver, effect, control);
1317  return Replace(receiver);
1318  }
1319 
1320  // Check whether {receiver} is a spec object.
1321  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsReceiver(), receiver);
1322  Node* branch =
1323  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
1324 
1325  Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
1326  Node* etrue = effect;
1327  Node* rtrue = receiver;
1328 
1329  Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
1330  Node* efalse = effect;
1331  Node* rfalse;
1332  {
1333  // Convert {receiver} using the ToObjectStub.
1334  Callable callable = Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtin::kToObject);
1335  auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
1336  graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
1337  callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(),
1338  CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState, node->op()->properties());
1339  Node* call = rfalse = efalse = if_false =
1340  graph()->NewNode(common()->Call(call_descriptor),
1341  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code()),
1342  receiver, context, frame_state, efalse, if_false);
1343 
1344  // We preserve the type of {node}. This is generally useful (to enable
1345  // type-based optimizations), and is also required in order to help
1346  // verification of TypeGuards.
1347  NodeProperties::SetType(call, NodeProperties::GetType(node));
1348  }
1349 
1350  // Update potential {IfException} uses of {node} to point to the above
1351  // ToObject stub call node instead. Note that the stub can only throw on
1352  // receivers that can be null or undefined.
1353  Node* on_exception = nullptr;
1354  if (receiver_type.Maybe(Type::NullOrUndefined()) &&
1355  NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
1356  NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(on_exception, if_false);
1357  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(on_exception, efalse);
1358  if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), if_false);
1359  Revisit(on_exception);
1360  }
1361 
1362  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
1363  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
1364 
1365  // Morph the {node} into an appropriate Phi.
1366  ReplaceWithValue(node, node, effect, control);
1367  node->ReplaceInput(0, rtrue);
1368  node->ReplaceInput(1, rfalse);
1369  node->ReplaceInput(2, control);
1370  node->TrimInputCount(3);
1371  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node,
1372  common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2));
1373  return Changed(node);
1374 }

1391 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSHasInPrototypeChain(Node* node) {
1392  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSHasInPrototypeChain, node->opcode());
1393  Node* value = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
1394  Type value_type = NodeProperties::GetType(value);
1395  Node* prototype = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
1396  Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
1397  Node* frame_state = NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node);
1398  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
1399  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
1400 
1401  // If {value} cannot be a receiver, then it cannot have {prototype} in
1402  // it's prototype chain (all Primitive values have a null prototype).
1403  if (value_type.Is(Type::Primitive())) {
1404  value = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
1405  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
1406  return Replace(value);
1407  }
1408 
1409  Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), value);
1410  Node* branch0 =
1411  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check0, control);
1412 
1413  Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
1414  Node* etrue0 = effect;
1415  Node* vtrue0 = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
1416 
1417  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
1418 
1419  // Loop through the {value}s prototype chain looking for the {prototype}.
1420  Node* loop = control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Loop(2), control, control);
1421  Node* eloop = effect =
1422  graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), effect, effect, loop);
1423  Node* terminate = graph()->NewNode(common()->Terminate(), eloop, loop);
1424  MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), terminate);
1425  Node* vloop = value = graph()->NewNode(
1426  common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2), value, value, loop);
1427  NodeProperties::SetType(vloop, Type::NonInternal());
1428 
1429  // Load the {value} map and instance type.
1430  Node* value_map = effect = graph()->NewNode(
1431  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()), value, effect, control);
1432  Node* value_instance_type = effect = graph()->NewNode(
1433  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapInstanceType()), value_map,
1434  effect, control);
1435 
1436  // Check if the {value} is a special receiver, because for special
1437  // receivers, i.e. proxies or API values that need access checks,
1438  // we have to use the %HasInPrototypeChain runtime function instead.
1439  Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(
1440  simplified()->NumberLessThanOrEqual(), value_instance_type,
1441  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(LAST_SPECIAL_RECEIVER_TYPE));
1442  Node* branch1 =
1443  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check1, control);
1444 
1445  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
1446 
1447  Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1);
1448  Node* etrue1 = effect;
1449  Node* vtrue1;
1450 
1451  // Check if the {value} is not a receiver at all.
1452  Node* check10 =
1453  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), value_instance_type,
1454  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE));
1455  Node* branch10 =
1456  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check10, if_true1);
1457 
1458  // A primitive value cannot match the {prototype} we're looking for.
1459  if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch10);
1460  vtrue1 = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
1461 
1462  Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch10);
1463  Node* efalse1 = etrue1;
1464  Node* vfalse1;
1465  {
1466  // Slow path, need to call the %HasInPrototypeChain runtime function.
1467  vfalse1 = efalse1 = if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(
1468  javascript()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kHasInPrototypeChain), value,
1469  prototype, context, frame_state, efalse1, if_false1);
1470 
1471  // Replace any potential {IfException} uses of {node} to catch
1472  // exceptions from this %HasInPrototypeChain runtime call instead.
1473  Node* on_exception = nullptr;
1474  if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
1475  NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(on_exception, vfalse1);
1476  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(on_exception, efalse1);
1477  if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), vfalse1);
1478  Revisit(on_exception);
1479  }
1480  }
1481 
1482  // Load the {value} prototype.
1483  Node* value_prototype = effect = graph()->NewNode(
1484  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapPrototype()), value_map,
1485  effect, control);
1486 
1487  // Check if we reached the end of {value}s prototype chain.
1488  Node* check2 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(),
1489  value_prototype, jsgraph()->NullConstant());
1490  Node* branch2 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check2, control);
1491 
1492  Node* if_true2 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch2);
1493  Node* etrue2 = effect;
1494  Node* vtrue2 = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
1495 
1496  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch2);
1497 
1498  // Check if we reached the {prototype}.
1499  Node* check3 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(),
1500  value_prototype, prototype);
1501  Node* branch3 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check3, control);
1502 
1503  Node* if_true3 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch3);
1504  Node* etrue3 = effect;
1505  Node* vtrue3 = jsgraph()->TrueConstant();
1506 
1507  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch3);
1508 
1509  // Close the loop.
1510  vloop->ReplaceInput(1, value_prototype);
1511  eloop->ReplaceInput(1, effect);
1512  loop->ReplaceInput(1, control);
1513 
1514  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(5), if_true0, if_true1, if_true2,
1515  if_true3, if_false1);
1516  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(5), etrue0, etrue1, etrue2,
1517  etrue3, efalse1, control);
1518 
1519  // Morph the {node} into an appropriate Phi.
1520  ReplaceWithValue(node, node, effect, control);
1521  node->ReplaceInput(0, vtrue0);
1522  node->ReplaceInput(1, vtrue1);
1523  node->ReplaceInput(2, vtrue2);
1524  node->ReplaceInput(3, vtrue3);
1525  node->ReplaceInput(4, vfalse1);
1526  node->ReplaceInput(5, control);
1527  node->TrimInputCount(6);
1528  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node,
1529  common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 5));
1530  return Changed(node);
1531 }

1533 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSOrdinaryHasInstance(Node* node) {
1534  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSOrdinaryHasInstance, node->opcode());
1535  Node* constructor = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);

1561 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSHasContextExtension(Node* node) {
1562  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSHasContextExtension, node->opcode());
1563  size_t depth = OpParameter<size_t>(node->op());
1564  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
1565  TNode<Context> context =
1566  TNode<Context>::UncheckedCast(NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node));
1567  Node* control = graph()->start();
1568 
1569  JSGraphAssembler gasm(broker(), jsgraph_, jsgraph_->zone(),
1570  BranchSemantics::kJS);
1571  gasm.InitializeEffectControl(effect, control);
1572 
1573  for (size_t i = 0; i < depth; ++i) {
1574  context = gasm.LoadField<Context>(
1575  AccessBuilder::ForContextSlotKnownPointer(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX),
1576  context);
1577  }
1578  TNode<ScopeInfo> scope_info = gasm.LoadField<ScopeInfo>(
1579  AccessBuilder::ForContextSlot(Context::SCOPE_INFO_INDEX), context);
1580  TNode<Word32T> scope_info_flags = gasm.EnterMachineGraph<Word32T>(
1581  gasm.LoadField<Word32T>(AccessBuilder::ForScopeInfoFlags(), scope_info),
1582  UseInfo::TruncatingWord32());
1583  TNode<Word32T> flags_masked = gasm.Word32And(
1584  scope_info_flags,
1585  gasm.Uint32Constant(ScopeInfo::HasContextExtensionSlotBit::kMask));
1586  TNode<Word32T> no_extension =
1587  gasm.Word32Equal(flags_masked, gasm.Uint32Constant(0));
1588  TNode<Word32T> has_extension =
1589  gasm.Word32Equal(no_extension, gasm.Uint32Constant(0));
1590  TNode<Boolean> has_extension_boolean = gasm.ExitMachineGraph<Boolean>(
1591  has_extension, MachineRepresentation::kBit, Type::Boolean());
1592 
1593  ReplaceWithValue(node, has_extension_boolean, gasm.effect(), gasm.control());
1594  return Changed(node);
1595 }

1618 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSLoadContext(Node* node) {
1619  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSLoadContext, node->opcode());
1620  ContextAccess const& access = ContextAccessOf(node->op());
1621  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
1622  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
1623  JSGraphAssembler gasm(broker(), jsgraph(), jsgraph()->zone(),
1624  BranchSemantics::kJS);
1625  gasm.InitializeEffectControl(effect, control);
1626 
1627  TNode<Context> context =
1628  TNode<Context>::UncheckedCast(NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node));
1629  for (size_t i = 0; i < access.depth(); ++i) {
1630  context = gasm.LoadField<Context>(
1631  AccessBuilder::ForContextSlotKnownPointer(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX),
1632  context);
1633  }
1634 
1635  TNode<Object> value = gasm.LoadField<Object>(
1636  AccessBuilder::ForContextSlot(access.index()), context);
1637  TNode<Object> result =
1638  gasm.SelectIf<Object>(gasm.ObjectIsSmi(value))
1639  .Then([&] { return value; })
1640  .Else([&] {
1641  TNode<Map> value_map =
1642  gasm.LoadMap(TNode<HeapObject>::UncheckedCast(value));
1643  return gasm.SelectIf<Object>(gasm.IsContextCellMap(value_map))
1644  .Then([&] {
1645  TNode<HeapObject> heap_value =
1646  TNode<HeapObject>::UncheckedCast(value);
1647  TNode<Int32T> state = gasm.LoadField<Int32T>(
1648  AccessBuilder::ForContextCellState(), heap_value);
1649  static_assert(ContextCell::State::kConst == 0);
1650  static_assert(ContextCell::State::kSmi == 1);
1651  return gasm
1652  .MachineSelectIf<Object>(gasm.Int32LessThanOrEqual(
1653  state, gasm.Int32Constant(ContextCell::kSmi)))
1654  .Then([&] {
1655  return gasm.LoadField<Object>(
1656  AccessBuilder::ForContextCellTaggedValue(),
1657  heap_value);
1658  })
1659  .Else([&] {
1660  return gasm
1661  .MachineSelectIf<Object>(gasm.Word32Equal(
1662  state, gasm.Int32Constant(ContextCell::kInt32)))
1663  .Then([&] {
1664  return gasm.LoadField<Number>(
1665  AccessBuilder::ForContextCellInt32Value(),
1666  heap_value);
1667  })
1668  .Else([&] {
1669  return gasm.LoadField<Number>(
1670  AccessBuilder::ForContextCellFloat64Value(),
1671  heap_value);
1672  })
1673  .Value();
1674  })
1675  .Value();
1676  })
1677  .Else([&] { return value; })
1678  .ExpectFalse()
1679  .Value();
1680  })
1681  .Value();
1682 
1683  ReplaceWithValue(node, result, gasm.effect(), gasm.control());
1684  return Changed(node);

1687 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSStoreContextNoCell(Node* node) {

1709 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSStoreContext(Node* node) {
1710  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSStoreContext, node->opcode());
1711  ContextAccess const& access = ContextAccessOf(node->op());
1712  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
1713  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
1714  FrameState frame_state{NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node)};
1715  JSGraphAssembler gasm(broker(), jsgraph(), jsgraph()->zone(),
1716  BranchSemantics::kJS);
1717  gasm.InitializeEffectControl(effect, control);
1718 
1719  TNode<Context> context =
1720  TNode<Context>::UncheckedCast(NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node));
1721  for (size_t i = 0; i < access.depth(); ++i) {
1722  context = gasm.LoadField<Context>(
1723  AccessBuilder::ForContextSlotKnownPointer(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX),
1724  context);
1725  }
1726 
1727  TNode<Object> old_value = gasm.LoadField<Object>(
1728  AccessBuilder::ForContextSlot(access.index()), context);
1729  TNode<Object> new_value =
1730  TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0));
1731 
1732  gasm.If(gasm.ObjectIsSmi(old_value))
1733  .Then([&] {
1734  gasm.StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForContextSlot(access.index()), context,
1735  new_value);
1736  })
1737  .Else([&] {
1738  TNode<Map> old_value_map =
1739  gasm.LoadMap(TNode<HeapObject>::UncheckedCast(old_value));
1740  gasm.If(gasm.IsContextCellMap(old_value_map))
1741  .Then([&] {
1742  gasm.DetachContextCell(context, new_value,
1743  static_cast<int>(access.index()),
1744  frame_state);
1745  })
1746  .Else([&] {
1747  gasm.StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForContextSlot(access.index()),
1748  context, new_value);
1749  })
1750  .ExpectFalse();
1751  });
1752 
1753  ReplaceWithValue(node, gasm.effect(), gasm.effect(), gasm.control());
1754  return Changed(node);
1755 }

1757 Node* JSTypedLowering::BuildGetModuleCell(Node* node) {
1758  DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadModule ||
1759  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSStoreModule);
1760  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
1761  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
1762 
1763  int32_t cell_index = OpParameter<int32_t>(node->op());
1764  Node* module = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
1765  Type module_type = NodeProperties::GetType(module);
1766 
1767  if (module_type.IsHeapConstant()) {
1768  SourceTextModuleRef module_constant =
1769  module_type.AsHeapConstant()->Ref().AsSourceTextModule();
1770  OptionalCellRef cell_constant =
1771  module_constant.GetCell(broker(), cell_index);
1772  if (cell_constant.has_value())
1773  return jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(*cell_constant, broker());
1774  }
1775 
1776  FieldAccess field_access;
1777  int index;
1778  if (SourceTextModuleDescriptor::GetCellIndexKind(cell_index) ==
1779  SourceTextModuleDescriptor::kExport) {
1780  field_access = AccessBuilder::ForModuleRegularExports();
1781  index = cell_index - 1;
1782  } else {
1783  DCHECK_EQ(SourceTextModuleDescriptor::GetCellIndexKind(cell_index),
1784  SourceTextModuleDescriptor::kImport);
1785  field_access = AccessBuilder::ForModuleRegularImports();
1786  index = -cell_index - 1;
1787  }
1788  Node* array = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(field_access),
1789  module, effect, control);
1790  return graph()->NewNode(
1791  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArraySlot(index)), array,
1792  effect, control);
1793 }

1831 void ReduceBuiltin(JSGraph* jsgraph, Node* node, Builtin builtin, int arity,
1832  CallDescriptor::Flags flags) {
1833  // Patch {node} to a direct CEntry call.
1834  // ----------- A r g u m e n t s -----------
1835  // -- 0: CEntry
1836  // --- Stack args ---
1837  // -- 1: new_target
1838  // -- 2: target
1839  // -- 3: argc, including the receiver and implicit args (Smi)
1840  // -- 4: padding
1841  // -- 5: receiver
1842  // -- [6, 6 + n[: the n actual arguments passed to the builtin
1843  // --- Register args ---
1844  // -- 6 + n: the C entry point
1845  // -- 6 + n + 1: argc (Int32)
1846  // -----------------------------------
1847 
1848  // These SBXCHECKs are a defense-in-depth measure to ensure that we always
1849  // generate valid calls here (with matching signatures).
1850  SBXCHECK(Builtins::IsCpp(builtin));
1851  SBXCHECK_GE(arity + kJSArgcReceiverSlots,
1852  Builtins::GetFormalParameterCount(builtin));
1853 
1854  // The logic contained here is mirrored in Builtins::Generate_Adaptor.
1855  // Keep these in sync.
1856 
1857  Node* target = node->InputAt(JSCallOrConstructNode::TargetIndex());
1858 
1859  // Unify representations between construct and call nodes. For construct
1860  // nodes, the receiver is undefined. For call nodes, the new_target is
1861  // undefined.
1862  Node* new_target;
1863  Zone* zone = jsgraph->zone();
1864  if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSConstruct) {
1865  static_assert(JSCallNode::ReceiverIndex() ==
1866  JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex());
1867  new_target = JSConstructNode{node}.new_target();
1868  node->ReplaceInput(JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex(),
1869  jsgraph->UndefinedConstant());
1870  node->RemoveInput(JSConstructNode{node}.FeedbackVectorIndex());
1871  } else {
1872  new_target = jsgraph->UndefinedConstant();
1873  node->RemoveInput(JSCallNode{node}.FeedbackVectorIndex());
1874  }
1875 
1876  // CPP builtins are implemented in C++, and we can inline it.
1877  // CPP builtins create a builtin exit frame.
1878  const bool has_builtin_exit_frame = true;
1879 
1880  Node* stub =
1881  jsgraph->CEntryStubConstant(1, ArgvMode::kStack, has_builtin_exit_frame);
1882  node->ReplaceInput(0, stub);
1883 
1884  const int argc = arity + BuiltinArguments::kNumExtraArgsWithReceiver;
1885  Node* argc_node = jsgraph->ConstantNoHole(argc);
1886 
1887  static const int kStub = 1;
1888  static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kNewTargetIndex == 0);
1889  static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kTargetIndex == 1);
1890  static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kArgcIndex == 2);
1891  static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kPaddingIndex == 3);
1892  node->InsertInput(zone, 1, new_target);
1893  node->InsertInput(zone, 2, target);
1894  node->InsertInput(zone, 3, argc_node);
1895  node->InsertInput(zone, 4, jsgraph->PaddingConstant());
1896  int cursor = arity + kStub + BuiltinArguments::kNumExtraArgsWithReceiver;
1897 
1898  Address entry = Builtins::CppEntryOf(builtin);
1899  ExternalReference entry_ref = ExternalReference::Create(entry);
1900  Node* entry_node = jsgraph->ExternalConstant(entry_ref);
1901 
1902  node->InsertInput(zone, cursor++, entry_node);
1903  node->InsertInput(zone, cursor++, argc_node);
1904 
1905  static const int kReturnCount = 1;
1906  const char* debug_name = Builtins::name(builtin);
1907  Operator::Properties properties = node->op()->properties();
1908  auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetCEntryStubCallDescriptor(
1909  zone, kReturnCount, argc, debug_name, properties, flags,
1910  StackArgumentOrder::kJS);
1911 
1912  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, jsgraph->common()->Call(call_descriptor));
1913 }

1916 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSConstructForwardVarargs(Node* node) {
1917  DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSConstructForwardVarargs, node->opcode());

1940  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 5, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());

1943  graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(), arity + 1,

1945  return Changed(node);
1946  }

1948  return NoChange();

2019 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSCall(Node* node) {
2020  JSCallNode n(node);
2021  CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2022  int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
2023  ConvertReceiverMode convert_mode = p.convert_mode();
2024  Node* target = n.target();
2025  Type target_type = NodeProperties::GetType(target);
2026  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
2027  Type receiver_type = NodeProperties::GetType(receiver);
2028  Effect effect = n.effect();
2029  Control control = n.control();
2030 
2031  // Try to infer receiver {convert_mode} from {receiver} type.
2032  if (receiver_type.Is(Type::NullOrUndefined())) {
2033  convert_mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined;
2034  } else if (!receiver_type.Maybe(Type::NullOrUndefined())) {
2035  convert_mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined;
2036  }
2037 
2038  // Check if we know the SharedFunctionInfo of {target}.
2039  OptionalJSFunctionRef function;
2040  OptionalSharedFunctionInfoRef shared;
2041 
2042  if (target_type.IsHeapConstant() &&
2043  target_type.AsHeapConstant()->Ref().IsJSFunction()) {
2044  function = target_type.AsHeapConstant()->Ref().AsJSFunction();
2045  shared = function->shared(broker());
2046  } else if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateClosure) {
2047  CreateClosureParameters const& ccp =
2048  JSCreateClosureNode{target}.Parameters();
2049  shared = ccp.shared_info();
2050  } else if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kCheckClosure) {
2051  FeedbackCellRef cell = MakeRef(broker(), FeedbackCellOf(target->op()));
2052  shared = cell.shared_function_info(broker());
2053  }
2054 
2055  if (shared.has_value()) {
2056  // Do not inline the call if we need to check whether to break at entry.
2057  // If this state changes during background compilation, the compilation
2058  // job will be aborted from the main thread (see
2059  // Debug::PrepareFunctionForDebugExecution()).
2060  if (shared->HasBreakInfo(broker())) return NoChange();
2061 
2062  // Class constructors are callable, but [[Call]] will raise an exception.
2063  // See ES6 section 9.2.1 [[Call]] ( thisArgument, argumentsList ).
2064  // We need to check here in addition to JSCallReducer for Realms.
2065  // TODO(pthier): Consolidate all the class constructor checks.
2066  if (IsClassConstructor(shared->kind())) return NoChange();
2067 
2068  // Check if we need to convert the {receiver}, but bailout if it would
2069  // require data from a foreign native context.
2070  if (is_sloppy(shared->language_mode()) && !shared->native() &&
2071  !receiver_type.Is(Type::Receiver())) {
2072  if (!function.has_value() || !function->native_context(broker()).equals(
2073  broker()->target_native_context())) {
2074  return NoChange();
2075  }
2076  NativeContextRef native_context = function->native_context(broker());
2077  Node* global_proxy = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
2078  native_context.global_proxy_object(broker()), broker());
2079  receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2080  simplified()->ConvertReceiver(convert_mode), receiver,
2081  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(native_context, broker()), global_proxy,
2082  effect, control);
2083  NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, receiver, 1);
2084  }
2085 
2086  // Load the context from the {target}.
2087  Node* context = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2088  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSFunctionContext()), target,
2089  effect, control);
2090  NodeProperties::ReplaceContextInput(node, context);
2091 
2092  // Update the effect dependency for the {node}.
2093  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
2094 
2095  // Compute flags for the call.
2096  CallDescriptor::Flags flags = CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState;
2097  Node* new_target = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
2098 
2099  // TODO(412398354): use the dispatch handle here to avoid a runtime check.
2100  int formal_count =
2101  shared->internal_formal_parameter_count_without_receiver_deprecated();
2102  if (formal_count > arity) {
2103  node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
2104  // Underapplication. Massage the arguments to match the expected number of
2105  // arguments.
2106  for (int i = arity; i < formal_count; i++) {
2107  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), arity + 2,
2108  jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
2109  }
2110 
2111  // Patch {node} to a direct call.
2112  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), formal_count + 2, new_target);
2113  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), formal_count + 3,
2114  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JSParameterCount(arity)));
2115 #ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
2116  node->InsertInput(
2117  graph()->zone(), formal_count + 4,
2118  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(kPlaceholderDispatchHandle.value()));
2119 #endif
2120  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node,
2121  common()->Call(Linkage::GetJSCallDescriptor(
2122  graph()->zone(), false, 1 + formal_count,
2123  flags | CallDescriptor::kCanUseRoots)));
2124  } else if (shared->HasBuiltinId() &&
2125  Builtins::IsCpp(shared->builtin_id())) {
2126  // Patch {node} to a direct CEntry call.
2127  ReduceBuiltin(jsgraph(), node, shared->builtin_id(), arity, flags);
2128  } else if (shared->HasBuiltinId()) {
2129  Builtin builtin = shared->builtin_id();
2130  DCHECK(Builtins::HasJSLinkage(builtin));
2131 
2132  // This SBXCHECK is a defense-in-depth measure to ensure that we always
2133  // generate valid calls here (with matching signatures).
2134  SBXCHECK_GE(arity + kJSArgcReceiverSlots,
2135  Builtins::GetFormalParameterCount(builtin));
2136 
2137  // Patch {node} to a direct code object call.
2138  Callable callable = Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), builtin);
2139 
2140  const CallInterfaceDescriptor& descriptor = callable.descriptor();
2141  auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
2142  graph()->zone(), descriptor, 1 + arity, flags);
2143  Node* stub_code = jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code());
2144  node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
2145  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 0, stub_code); // Code object.
2146  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 2, new_target);
2147  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 3,
2148  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JSParameterCount(arity)));
2149 #ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
2150  node->InsertInput(
2151  graph()->zone(), 4,
2152  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(kPlaceholderDispatchHandle.value()));
2153 #endif
2154  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, common()->Call(call_descriptor));
2155  } else {
2156  // Patch {node} to a direct call.
2157  node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
2158  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), arity + 2, new_target);
2159  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), arity + 3,
2160  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JSParameterCount(arity)));
2161 #ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
2162  node->InsertInput(
2163  graph()->zone(), arity + 4,
2164  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(kPlaceholderDispatchHandle.value()));
2165 #endif
2166  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node,
2167  common()->Call(Linkage::GetJSCallDescriptor(
2168  graph()->zone(), false, 1 + arity,
2169  flags | CallDescriptor::kCanUseRoots)));
2170  }
2171  return Changed(node);
2172  }
2173 
2174  // Check if {target} is a directly callable JSFunction.
2175  if (target_type.Is(Type::CallableFunction())) {
2176  // The node will change operators, remove the feedback vector.
2177  node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
2178  // Compute flags for the call.
2179  CallDescriptor::Flags flags = CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState;
2180  // Patch {node} to an indirect call via the CallFunction builtin.
2181  Callable callable = CodeFactory::CallFunction(isolate(), convert_mode);
2182  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 0,
2183  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code()));
2184  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 2,
2185  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JSParameterCount(arity)));
2186  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
2187  node, common()->Call(Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
2188  graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(), 1 + arity, flags)));
2189  return Changed(node);
2190  }
2191 
2192  // Maybe we did at least learn something about the {receiver}.
2193  if (p.convert_mode() != convert_mode) {
2194  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
2195  node,
2196  javascript()->Call(p.arity(), p.frequency(), p.feedback(), convert_mode,
2197  p.speculation_mode(), p.feedback_relation()));
2198  return Changed(node);
2199  }
2200 
2201  return NoChange();
2202 }

2204 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSForInNext(Node* node) {
2205  JSForInNextNode n(node);
2206  Node* receiver = n.receiver();
2207  Node* cache_array = n.cache_array();
2208  Node* cache_type = n.cache_type();
2209  Node* index = n.index();
2210  Node* context = n.context();
2211  FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
2212  Effect effect = n.effect();
2213  Control control = n.control();
2214 
2215  // Load the map of the {receiver}.
2216  Node* receiver_map = effect =
2217  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()),
2218  receiver, effect, control);
2219 
2220  switch (n.Parameters().mode()) {
2221  case ForInMode::kUseEnumCacheKeys:
2222  case ForInMode::kUseEnumCacheKeysAndIndices: {
2223  // Ensure that the expected map still matches that of the {receiver}.
2224  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(),
2225  receiver_map, cache_type);
2226  effect =
2227  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap),
2228  check, effect, control);
2229 
2230  // Since the change to LoadElement() below is effectful, we connect
2231  // node to all effect uses.
2232  ReplaceWithValue(node, node, node, control);
2233 
2234  // Morph the {node} into a LoadElement.
2235  node->ReplaceInput(0, cache_array);
2236  node->ReplaceInput(1, index);
2237  node->ReplaceInput(2, effect);
2238  node->ReplaceInput(3, control);
2239  node->TrimInputCount(4);
2240  ElementAccess access =
2241  AccessBuilder::ForJSForInCacheArrayElement(n.Parameters().mode());
2242  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, simplified()->LoadElement(access));
2243  NodeProperties::SetType(node, access.type);
2244  break;
2245  }
2246  case ForInMode::kGeneric: {
2247  // Load the next {key} from the {cache_array}.
2248  Node* key = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2249  simplified()->LoadElement(AccessBuilder::ForJSForInCacheArrayElement(
2250  n.Parameters().mode())),
2251  cache_array, index, effect, control);
2252 
2253  // Check if the expected map still matches that of the {receiver}.
2254  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(),
2255  receiver_map, cache_type);
2256  Node* branch =
2257  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
2258 
2259  Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
2260  Node* etrue;
2261  Node* vtrue;
2262  {
2263  // Don't need filtering since expected map still matches that of the
2264  // {receiver}.
2265  etrue = effect;
2266  vtrue = key;
2267  }
2268 
2269  Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
2270  Node* efalse;
2271  Node* vfalse;
2272  {
2273  // Filter the {key} to check if it's still a valid property of the
2274  // {receiver} (does the ToName conversion implicitly).
2275  Callable const callable =
2276  Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtin::kForInFilter);
2277  auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
2278  graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
2279  callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(),
2280  CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
2281  vfalse = efalse = if_false = graph()->NewNode(
2282  common()->Call(call_descriptor),
2283  jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code()), key, receiver,
2284  context, frame_state, effect, if_false);
2285  NodeProperties::SetType(
2286  vfalse,
2287  Type::Union(Type::String(), Type::Undefined(), graph()->zone()));
2288 
2289  // Update potential {IfException} uses of {node} to point to the above
2290  // ForInFilter stub call node instead.
2291  Node* if_exception = nullptr;
2292  if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &if_exception)) {
2293  if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), vfalse);
2294  NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(if_exception, vfalse);
2295  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(if_exception, efalse);
2296  Revisit(if_exception);
2297  }
2298  }
2299 
2300  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
2301  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
2302  ReplaceWithValue(node, node, effect, control);
2303 
2304  // Morph the {node} into a Phi.
2305  node->ReplaceInput(0, vtrue);
2306  node->ReplaceInput(1, vfalse);
2307  node->ReplaceInput(2, control);
2308  node->TrimInputCount(3);
2309  NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
2310  node, common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2));
2311  }
2312  }
2313 
2314  return Changed(node);
2315 }

2317 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSForInPrepare(Node* node) {
2318  JSForInPrepareNode n(node);
2319  Node* enumerator = n.enumerator();
2320  Effect effect = n.effect();
2321  Control control = n.control();
2322  Node* cache_type = enumerator;
2323  Node* cache_array = nullptr;
2324  Node* cache_length = nullptr;
2325 
2326  switch (n.Parameters().mode()) {
2327  case ForInMode::kUseEnumCacheKeys:
2328  case ForInMode::kUseEnumCacheKeysAndIndices: {
2329  // Check that the {enumerator} is a Map.
2330  // The direct IsMap check requires reading of an instance type, so we
2331  // compare its map against fixed_array_map instead (by definition,
2332  // the {enumerator} is either the receiver's Map or a FixedArray).
2333  Node* check_for_fixed_array = effect =
2334  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CompareMaps(
2335  ZoneRefSet<Map>(broker()->fixed_array_map())),
2336  enumerator, effect, control);
2337  Node* check_for_not_fixed_array =
2338  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->BooleanNot(), check_for_fixed_array);
2339  effect =
2340  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap),
2341  check_for_not_fixed_array, effect, control);
2342 
2343  // Load the enum cache from the {enumerator} map.
2344  Node* descriptor_array = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2345  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapDescriptors()),
2346  enumerator, effect, control);
2347  Node* enum_cache = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2348  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForDescriptorArrayEnumCache()),
2349  descriptor_array, effect, control);
2350  cache_array = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2351  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForEnumCacheKeys()),
2352  enum_cache, effect, control);
2353 
2354  // Load the enum length of the {enumerator} map.
2355  Node* bit_field3 = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2356  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField3()), enumerator,
2357  effect, control);
2358  static_assert(Map::Bits3::EnumLengthBits::kShift == 0);
2359  cache_length = graph()->NewNode(
2360  simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), bit_field3,
2361  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(Map::Bits3::EnumLengthBits::kMask));
2362  break;
2363  }
2364  case ForInMode::kGeneric: {
2365  // Check if the {enumerator} is a Map or a FixedArray.
2366  // The direct IsMap check requires reading of an instance type, so we
2367  // compare against fixed array map instead (by definition,
2368  // the {enumerator} is either the receiver's Map or a FixedArray).
2369  Node* check = effect =
2370  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CompareMaps(
2371  ZoneRefSet<Map>(broker()->fixed_array_map())),
2372  enumerator, effect, control);
2373  Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse),
2374  check, control);
2375 
2376  Node* if_map = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
2377  Node* etrue = effect;
2378  Node* cache_array_true;
2379  Node* cache_length_true;
2380  {
2381  // Load the enum cache from the {enumerator} map.
2382  Node* descriptor_array = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
2383  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapDescriptors()),
2384  enumerator, etrue, if_map);
2385  Node* enum_cache = etrue =
2386  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(
2387  AccessBuilder::ForDescriptorArrayEnumCache()),
2388  descriptor_array, etrue, if_map);
2389  cache_array_true = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
2390  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForEnumCacheKeys()),
2391  enum_cache, etrue, if_map);
2392 
2393  // Load the enum length of the {enumerator} map.
2394  Node* bit_field3 = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
2395  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField3()),
2396  enumerator, etrue, if_map);
2397  static_assert(Map::Bits3::EnumLengthBits::kShift == 0);
2398  cache_length_true = graph()->NewNode(
2399  simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), bit_field3,
2400  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(Map::Bits3::EnumLengthBits::kMask));
2401  }
2402 
2403  Node* if_fixed_array = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
2404  Node* efalse = effect;
2405  Node* cache_array_false;
2406  Node* cache_length_false;
2407  {
2408  // The {enumerator} is the FixedArray with the keys to iterate.
2409  cache_array_false = enumerator;
2410  cache_length_false = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
2411  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayLength()),
2412  cache_array_false, efalse, if_fixed_array);
2413  }
2414 
2415  // Rewrite the uses of the {node}.
2416  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_map, if_fixed_array);
2417  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
2418  cache_array =
2419  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
2420  cache_array_true, cache_array_false, control);
2421  cache_length =
2422  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
2423  cache_length_true, cache_length_false, control);
2424  break;
2425  }
2426  }
2427 
2428  // Update the uses of {node}.
2429  for (Edge edge : node->use_edges()) {
2430  Node* const user = edge.from();
2431  if (NodeProperties::IsEffectEdge(edge)) {
2432  edge.UpdateTo(effect);
2433  Revisit(user);
2434  } else if (NodeProperties::IsControlEdge(edge)) {
2435  edge.UpdateTo(control);
2436  Revisit(user);
2437  } else {
2438  DCHECK(NodeProperties::IsValueEdge(edge));
2439  switch (ProjectionIndexOf(user->op())) {
2440  case 0:
2441  Replace(user, cache_type);
2442  break;
2443  case 1:
2444  Replace(user, cache_array);
2445  break;
2446  case 2:
2447  Replace(user, cache_length);
2448  break;
2449  default:
2450  UNREACHABLE();
2451  }
2452  }
2453  }
2454  node->Kill();
2455  return Replace(effect);
2456 }
