2593 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceObjectIsArray(Node* node) {
2594  Node* value = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
2595  Type value_type = NodeProperties::GetType(value);
2596  Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
2597  Node* frame_state = NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node);
2598  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
2599  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
2600 
2601  // Constant-fold based on {value} type.
2602  if (value_type.Is(Type::Array())) {
2603  value = jsgraph()->TrueConstant();
2604  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2605  return Replace(value);
2606  } else if (!value_type.Maybe(Type::ArrayOrProxy())) {
2607  value = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
2608  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2609  return Replace(value);
2610  }
2611 
2612  int count = 0;
2613  Node* values[5];
2614  Node* effects[5];
2615  Node* controls[4];
2616 
2617  // Check if the {value} is a Smi.
2618  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), value);
2619  control =
2620  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check, control);
2621 
2622  // The {value} is a Smi.
2623  controls[count] = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control);
2624  effects[count] = effect;
2625  values[count] = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
2626  count++;
2627 
2628  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control);
2629 
2630  // Load the {value}s instance type.
2631  Node* value_map = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2632  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()), value, effect, control);
2633  Node* value_instance_type = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2634  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapInstanceType()), value_map,
2635  effect, control);
2636 
2637  // Check if the {value} is a JSArray.
2638  check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), value_instance_type,
2639  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JS_ARRAY_TYPE));
2640  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, control);
2641 
2642  // The {value} is a JSArray.
2643  controls[count] = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control);
2644  effects[count] = effect;
2645  values[count] = jsgraph()->TrueConstant();
2646  count++;
2647 
2648  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control);
2649 
2650  // Check if the {value} is a JSProxy.
2651  check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), value_instance_type,
2652  jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JS_PROXY_TYPE));
2653  control =
2654  graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check, control);
2655 
2656  // The {value} is neither a JSArray nor a JSProxy.
2657  controls[count] = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control);
2658  effects[count] = effect;
2659  values[count] = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
2660  count++;
2661 
2662  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control);
2663 
2664  // Let the %ArrayIsArray runtime function deal with the JSProxy {value}.
2665  value = effect = control =
2666  graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kArrayIsArray), value,
2667  context, frame_state, effect, control);
2668  NodeProperties::SetType(value, Type::Boolean());
2669 
2670  // Update potential {IfException} uses of {node} to point to the above
2671  // %ArrayIsArray runtime call node instead.
2672  Node* on_exception = nullptr;
2673  if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
2674  NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(on_exception, control);
2675  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(on_exception, effect);
2676  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control);
2677  Revisit(on_exception);
2678  }
2679 
2680  // The {value} is neither a JSArray nor a JSProxy.
2681  controls[count] = control;
2682  effects[count] = effect;
2683  values[count] = value;
2684  count++;
2685 
2686  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(count), count, controls);
2687  effects[count] = control;
2688  values[count] = control;
2689  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(count), count + 1, effects);
2690  value = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, count),
2691  count + 1, values);
2692  ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
2693  return Replace(value);
2694 }

2696 Reduction JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSParseInt(Node* node) {
2697  Node* value = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
2698  Type value_type = NodeProperties::GetType(value);
2699  Node* radix = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
2700  Type radix_type = NodeProperties::GetType(radix);
2701  // We need kTenOrUndefined and kZeroOrUndefined because
2702  // the type representing {0,10} would become the range 1-10.
2703  if (value_type.Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger) &&
2704  (radix_type.Is(type_cache_->kTenOrUndefined) ||
2705  radix_type.Is(type_cache_->kZeroOrUndefined))) {
2706  // Number.parseInt(a:safe-integer) -> a
2707  // Number.parseInt(a:safe-integer,b:#0\/undefined) -> a
2708  // Number.parseInt(a:safe-integer,b:#10\/undefined) -> a
2709  ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2710  return Replace(value);
2711  }
2712  return NoChange();
2713 }

2731 Reduction JSTypedLowering::Reduce(Node* node) {
2732  switch (node->opcode()) {
2733  case IrOpcode::kJSEqual:
2734  return ReduceJSEqual(node);
2735  case IrOpcode::kJSStrictEqual:
2736  return ReduceJSStrictEqual(node);
2737  case IrOpcode::kJSLessThan: // fall through
2738  case IrOpcode::kJSGreaterThan: // fall through
2739  case IrOpcode::kJSLessThanOrEqual: // fall through
2740  case IrOpcode::kJSGreaterThanOrEqual:
2741  return ReduceJSComparison(node);
2742  case IrOpcode::kJSBitwiseOr:
2743  case IrOpcode::kJSBitwiseXor:
2744  case IrOpcode::kJSBitwiseAnd:
2745  return ReduceInt32Binop(node);
2746  case IrOpcode::kJSShiftLeft:
2747  case IrOpcode::kJSShiftRight:
2748  return ReduceUI32Shift(node, kSigned);
2749  case IrOpcode::kJSShiftRightLogical:
2750  return ReduceUI32Shift(node, kUnsigned);
2751  case IrOpcode::kJSAdd:
2752  return ReduceJSAdd(node);
2753  case IrOpcode::kJSSubtract:
2754  case IrOpcode::kJSMultiply:
2755  case IrOpcode::kJSDivide:
2756  case IrOpcode::kJSModulus:
2757  case IrOpcode::kJSExponentiate:
2758  return ReduceNumberBinop(node);
2759  case IrOpcode::kJSBitwiseNot:
2760  return ReduceJSBitwiseNot(node);
2761  case IrOpcode::kJSDecrement:
2762  return ReduceJSDecrement(node);
2763  case IrOpcode::kJSIncrement:
2764  return ReduceJSIncrement(node);
2765  case IrOpcode::kJSNegate:
2766  return ReduceJSNegate(node);
2767  case IrOpcode::kJSHasInPrototypeChain:
2768  return ReduceJSHasInPrototypeChain(node);
2769  case IrOpcode::kJSOrdinaryHasInstance:
2770  return ReduceJSOrdinaryHasInstance(node);
2771  case IrOpcode::kJSToLength:
2772  return ReduceJSToLength(node);
